author: Doug Knoop
title: Oct. 15 TV Picks: ‘Sleepy Hollow’ on Fox
text:
Unlimited Digital Access. $1 for 4 weeks. 
“High School Football,” 7 p.m. (ROOT): Skyline at Bothell (Live). 
“Heroes Reborn,” 8 p.m. (NBC): Miko’s plan may end in trouble; Malina gets closer to the truth; Luke confronts his past; Erica’s plans are confirmed. 
“The Originals,” 9 p.m. (The CW): Jackson and Elijah become worried about Hayley’s safety; Cami shares her theory on the murders with Klaus; Lucien has an unsettling warning for Elijah. 
“Project Runway,” 9 p.m. (Lifetime): The designers use 3-D printing technology to create avant-garde looks in a fashion-forward challenge. 
“How to Get Away with Murder,” 10 p.m. (ABC): Annalise and her team represent a suspect in the case of a murdered teen; Asher encounters a shocking confession; Wes gains more information about Rebecca’s disappearance. 
“Miss Fisher’s Murder Mysteries,” 10:33 p.m. (KCTS): An Australian Rules Football captain is found hanging by a rival team’s scarf. The New York Times
